This paper deals with network interfaces and their power consumption, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses algorithms for optimizing power consumption, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of these algorithms on Internet traffic, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the energy efficiency of the proposed algorithms, which could fall under the category of performance (cs.PF).
